<HEADLINE>
FT  27 MAR 93 / International Company News: Breedon drops 34% to Pounds
1.82m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Breedon, the limestone quarry operator and housebuilder, suffered a 34 per
cent fall in pre-tax profits from Pounds 2.76m to Pounds 1.82m, for the year
ended January 31.
Group turnover fell by 8 per cent to Pounds 8.73m (Pounds 9.49m) but an
increase since October in turnover of the core quarrying business, gave the
Derbyshire-based group cause for cautious optimism.
The housing market was still in the doldrums, the directors said.
An unchanged final dividend of 2.85p is proposed making a maintained total
for the year of 4.6p.
Earnings per share were shown as 4.41p down from a previous 6.85p.
