<HEADLINE>
FT  27 MAR 93 / Finance and the Family: National Insurance cards retire - At
a Glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
National Insurance cards and stamps are being abolished after 81 years. In
future, contributors will pay by direct debit or by a quarterly billing
system, with payments made via the Post Office or banks. The change mainly
affects the self-employed.
</TEXT>
<XX>
