<HEADLINE>
FT  27 MAR 93 / Finance and the Family: BT shares on shopping list - At a
Glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The government will use its third sale of shares in British Telecom, known
as BT III, to promote its share shop idea. Around 100 intermediaries met
with the Treasury this week to discuss the concept; they will be entitled to
display a new share shop logo and investors who apply through share shops
will receive preference in allocation. The earliest date for BT III would be
mid-July.
</TEXT>
