<HEADLINE>
FT  26 MAR 93 / Ford says strike had little impact
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SOME 8,000 white-collar staff at Ford held a 24-hour strike yesterday but
the company said the stoppage had not interrupted production on the
launch-day of the new Mondeo model.
Mr Jim Thomas, chief staff negotiator at Ford, said the strike had been 'a
total success' and had showed 'the depth of feeling' among the workforce
over the issue of compulsory redundancies.
The company is 80 jobs short of the 2,200 cuts it has been seeking by
voluntary means. It has said it will impose compulsory redundancies if it
does not reach its target by the end of this month.
</TEXT>
